ONNX Runtime's build system is based on CMake, and CMake doesn't know how the preinstalled libraries were built. For example, it finds libprotobuf.lib, but cmake has no way to know whether it was built in Debug mode or Release Mode, whether it was linked to static CRT or dynamic. You have to tell this information to cmake by setting cmake variables like Protobuf_USE_STATIC_LIBS. Therefore, if the preinstalled libs work, they work. If not, you can avoid this trouble by uninstalling them.
